metadata.name: Zena #139
metadata.description:
Zena is a study of creating complex patterns via manipulating particle angles using math, bitwise operators and noise.

It can take up to a minute to render or longer in low-performance computers. Enjoy the process!

----Best experienced in full screen----

Probabilities;

- 7 different patterns

- 4 frame types

- 2 frame colors

- 4 different particle hues (Rare; full spectrum) 

- Rare; circular placement

- Rare; dark background

You can right click and save as .png (or press 's' in liveMode) once the rendering is done.



Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, September 2022
@distcollective

metadata.name: Entropes #77
metadata.description:
Entropes is an abstract generative art project consisting of patterns and textures made with a heuristic rectangle packing algorithm. It’s a blend of shapes, geometry and colour. It draws notable inspiration from the Bauhaus art style. All these attributes are fused to form aesthetics that create diversity while maintaining cohesiveness across this body of work.

_____________________________________________________________________________________

The details go down to the very last pixel and outputs can be saved right from the browser at a full resolution of 6400 x 9600 pixels which ensures the quality holds up across majority of displays and different print sizes.

_____________________________________________________________________________________

Programmed entirely using p5js.

_____________________________________________________________________________________

A project by Kamau Kamau and Ian Wright

metadata.name: Twistings #160
metadata.description:
✧ TWISTINGS ✧

Twistings, the "Explore Variety" collection, explores the beauty & variety that is hidden within the simple math of Archimedean spirals.

There are seven different circular "entities", each brought forward by using slightly different mathematical settings of the spiral formulas: Drops, Circles, Fireworks, Flowers, Roses, Spirals & Twisters.

____

✧ CURATED / RANDOM ✧

I love both the concept of a heavily curated set, hand picked by the artist, the best representation / the most beautiful, but also the concept of the larger, random collections showing the variety hidden within the algorithm.

I've therefore also released an "Artist Curated" collection of 7 pieces that I meticulously hand-picked from over 1000 outputs. You can find these on the platform 1stDibs.com/nft (under my name "nadieh"). They represent my favorite for each of the seven unique entities. A free mint of this "Explore Variety" collection will be airdropped to each buyer of a "Curated" piece.

____

✧ OPTIONS ✧

n - Toggle grainy noise on/off (on by default, it's subtle to see)

s - Save the image at the current window size and pixel density

To save a larger image you can add the parameter `&pixeldensity=2` (or another number) to the end of the URL when viewed on the live page. Afterwards press "s" to save the image. The number is the factor with which the width and height are increased w.r.t. the current window size.

-- The larger the image / pixeldensity, the longer it will take to create & save --

____

✧ NOTES ✧

It works best and fastest in Firefox!

As of the drop day there is a browser bug for Chrome on the ARM Apple laptops. It incorrectly visualizes certain color blend modes. The following color palettes are affected: Antique, Camping, Pastel, Prime & Rainbow. I hope/assume this will be fixed soon. 

____

Created by Nadieh Bremer
Twitter & Instagram: @NadiehBremer
Website: VisualCinnamon.com

metadata.name: Millefoglie #430
metadata.description:
"A mille-feuille (French pronunciation: ​[mil fœj], "thousand-sheets"), also known by the names Napoleon, vanilla slice, and custard slice, is a dessert made of puff pastry layered with pastry cream. Its modern form was influenced by improvements made by Marie-Antoine Carême.

Traditionally, a mille-feuille is made up of three layers of puff pastry (pâte feuilletée), alternating with two layers of pastry cream (crème pâtissière). The top pastry layer is finished in various ways: sometimes it is topped with whipped cream, or it may be dusted with icing sugar, cocoa, pastry crumbs, or sliced almonds. It may also be glazed with icing or fondant alone, or in alternating white (icing) and brown (chocolate) or other colored icing stripes, and combed to create a marbled effect." — Wikipedia

Prints available upon request: prints@stefancontiero.com
Best enjoyed on browsers supporting Display-P3 color gamut.

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

@stefan_contiero

metadata.name: Unbalanced Life #23
metadata.description:
Most of the time we don't know what we do with our lives, we try hard and make decisions hoping for the best. We could go from a balanced and well-directed life to a disastrous and shattered one.

"Unbalanced Life" is an abstraction of these aspects. Each line represents a stage in your life. Over each line are "life decisions" that you take. Several are well defined, others are just a mess and explode, like in real life! 

The life type will be included below in the right corner unless your life is seriously "Shattered", then the name will be huge enough to punch you right in the face, or you could get "No Life" and with that, a disappointing tag will remember you that at less your life is better than this NFT.

What kind of life will you get?

You will face these challenging features:

Life types
- Shattered life
- Unbalanced life
- Balanced life
- Wasted life
- Lack of life
- No life 

Four color schemes
- Groovy seventies
- Rad 80's
- Fire and fury
- Outstanding carbon

Well-thought decisions
- Boolean

metadata.name: Skravert #101
metadata.description:
‘Skravert’ - Norwegian, verb, past tense. ‘The act of filling an area with lines; to shade an area’.

Skravert is a series of 320 sketches, each capturing the texture and feel of a material residing somewhere between cardboard and woolen rugs. The project is centred around rectangle subdivision and a line drawing algorithm, giving each piece its own unique expression when combined with a selection of 28 different color  palettes.  

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2021

metadata.name: Complicare #56
metadata.description:
Complicare is my first "still" generative work, and an exercise in minimalism.

Inspired by pioneers like Sol Lewitt and Frank Stella, as well as current fx_hash artists such as Rev Dan Catt and Yazid, this work attempts to balance a diverse visual output with a restricted generative system. I also wanted to focus on honing my abilities to add texture to the digital canvas, taking cues from other great artists on here like William Mapan and Hevey.

Each piece has one of 17 different layouts and one of 6 different color palettes.

Thanks to all of the artists on fx_hash for inspiring me every day to make more art, and particularly to dcarcher for some really insightful artistic perspective and feedback.

metadata.name: Sneronoi #25
metadata.description:
Stochastic neighbor embedding meets Voronoi tessellation.

Images are generated by gradient descent and the optimization process is shown as an animation. Each piece is considered final when the animation stops. There are 11 different color palettes and two distinct input point arrangements, allowing for a wide range of distinct visual outputs. Made with D3.

Press 's' to save as svg.

Press 'p' to save as png (4000x4000).

Author:
Claus O. Wilke
https://clauswilke.com/art
https://twitter.com/clauswilke

metadata.name: Grow Within Imperfection #25
metadata.description:
This piece was an interpretation of the feeling of imperfection and how we as humans grow to follow the flow of time without any possibility to turn back anything that happens during the process. The visual representation was a result of the interpreted idea's abstraction.

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the screen capture.

Made using Hydra (https://hydra.ojack.xyz/)

Rangga Purnama Aji, 2022
https://linktr.ee/ranggapuraji

metadata.name: Grande Dame #20
metadata.description:
Project inspired by the artworks of Vera Molnár ('Grande Dame' of digital art), one of the first women artists to use computers in her practice.

In January month of every year Π will party for Vera birth anniversary, artwork will come alive for the whole month.

Keys to interact:
[c] to change color mode (6 available)
[w] to raise wear level
[1] to [9] to change resolution
[s] to save as png (current settings)
[r] to reset all changes

Also in January:
[p] to pause/play animation
[r] to view standard artwork (paused)

Generative artwork by Gandhiavelli, @gandhiavelli. Made with p5js in 2022.
